cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper involves computer vision techniques for gait recognition using RGBD sensors, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes two new algorithms for feature extraction and uses a supervised classifier for person identification, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as another likely sub-category. The application of gait recognition for identity recognition to access restricted areas may also fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of inertial sensors and trajectory analysis may involve multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
